Representative Greene
1 moves to amend the bill on page 2, lines 11-20, by rewriting those lines to read:
2
3 "(7a) Prior express written consent. – An agreement that satisfies all the following
4 conditions:
5 a. It is in writing.
6 b. It bears the signature of the person called that clearly authorizes the
7 seller to deliver or cause to be delivered to the person called telephone
8 solicitations. The term 'signature' includes an electronic or digital form
9 of signature, to the extent that such form of signature is recognized as
10 a valid signature under applicable federal law or State law.
11 c. It includes the telephone number to which the signatory authorizes
12 such telephone solicitations to be delivered.
13 d. It includes a clear and conspicuous disclosure informing the person
14 signing both of the following:
15 1. By executing the agreement, such person authorizes the seller
16 to deliver or cause to be delivered to the signatory telephone
17 solicitations.
18 2. The person is not required to sign the agreement (directly or
19 indirectly) or agree to enter into such an agreement as a
20 condition of purchasing any property, goods, or services.".
